As long as there is no official API around it and you have queries with just one operation, you can use `queryManager` to find and refetch the query you need:

```dart
extension RefetchQueryByNameExtension on GraphQLClient {
  Future<void> refetchByName(String operationName) async {
    final toRefetch = queryManager.queries.values.firstWhereOrNull(
      (query) => query.options.document.definitions.any(
        (d) => d is OperationDefinitionNode && d.name?.value == operationName,
      ),
    );

    if (toRefetch != null) {
      queryManager.refetchQuery(toRefetch.queryId);
    }
  }
}
```
